# AIMS specification project — line-ending + binary classification
#
# Why this file: prevent CRLF/LF mixed-line-ending churn that surfaces when
# Windows contributors push (Windows core.autocrlf=true converts LF -> CRLF
# in the working tree on checkout, then back to LF on commit; without
# `text=auto eol=lf`, files can land in the index with CRLF endings or
# trigger "LF will be replaced by CRLF" warnings on every operation).
#
# Policy:
#   * text=auto eol=lf  — every text file normalizes to LF in the index
#                          and stays LF on Linux/macOS checkout. Windows
#                          contributors can have CRLF in working tree, but
#                          the canonical stored form is LF.
#   * <ext> binary       — don't try to normalize; keep bytes intact.
#
# Trigger to revisit: when adding a new binary file format (audio, video,
# fonts, archives, etc.), add an explicit `binary` line below.

* text=auto eol=lf

# Image / vector / document binaries
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif binary
*.ico binary
*.webp binary
*.pdf binary
*.docx binary
*.xlsx binary
*.pptx binary

# SVG is XML text but treated as binary to avoid line-ending churn on
# vector files that are typically authored once and rarely re-saved.
*.svg binary

# Archives + compressed
*.zip binary
*.tar binary
*.gz binary
*.tgz binary
*.bz2 binary
*.7z binary

# Audio / video
*.mp3 binary
*.mp4 binary
*.mov binary
*.webm binary

# Fonts
*.woff binary
*.woff2 binary
*.ttf binary
*.otf binary
*.eot binary
